{DIALOGUE}: I told you nice to shut the fuck up.
{DIALOGUE}: Now I'm gonna kill you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls out his gun and aims it at one of them, then the others.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All instinctively try to cover their heads.
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 21.
{META_DATA}: 49 CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Pick up the fuckin glass!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they dive to their knees to do what they're told, Laurie walks away with her son, who looks back over his shoulder at his father with his gun out.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 50 EXT. BANGKOK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank sits in the back of a motor samlor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bicycles dart around it like flies.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 51 - 52 OMIT 51 - 52 OMIT
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 53 INT. SOUL BROTHERS BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The clientele is almost exclusively black servicemen on R&R and Asian women.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A trio of ex-GI's plays authentic Southern blues on a small stage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ham hocks and collard greens come out of the kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Smoke chokes the place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank, one of the few men not in uniform, and not drunk or stoned, sits alone at a table with a Coca-Cola and surveys the activity: Dope being rolled.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dope being smoked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dope being shot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GI's and prostitutes climbing a staircase.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes follow an Army Master Sergeant, moving among the tables as if checking on the GI's well being.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But at some, his hand takes money, leaves in its place packets of powder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Sergeant feels eyes on him and glances up, catching Frank watching him from across the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He squints through the smoke at the figure at the table in the shadows, and, in a kind of shock, more to himself -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NATE
{DIALOGUE}: Frank - ?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank half-lifts his glass to wave, and Nate beams.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 54 INT. SOUL BROTHERS BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank has guests at his table now: his cousin Nate the Sergeant, and two young Asian wise guys.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They talk about him in Thai (subtitled):
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THAI
{DIALOGUE}: He say how much he wants?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NATE
{DIALOGUE}: He said "a lot."
{DIALOGUE}: What that means, I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: Four or five keys?
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 22.
{META_DATA}: 54 CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Thais regard Frank a moment, size him up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THAI
{DIALOGUE}: He's your cousin.
