{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: This is the jungle.
{DIALOGUE}: Tigers.
{DIALOGUE}: Vietcong.
{DIALOGUE}: The fuckin snakes alone will kill you.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: AA56 INT. NEW JERSEY BOARD OF BAR EXAMINERS - DAY AA56
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A room of student-type desks and no character.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie, and fifty others, have been here for hours taking the exam less than half of them will pass.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A56 EXT. JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A motley bunch of Thai thugs and black American soldiers with automatic weapons ride mules through the dense jungle with Nate and Frank, who - armed with a pistol, a rifle and ammo bandolier like Pancho Villa - is enjoying himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From his POV, the jungle canopy suddenly opens up on a poppy field the size of Manhattan.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank stares down at it.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: B56 EXT. JUNGLE RISE / OPIUM FARM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the ground now with their small private army, Nate speaks with one of the Thais, then translates for Frank.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NATE
{DIALOGUE}: He says this whole area's controlled by the Kuomintang - Chiang Kai-Shek's defeated army.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Some of whom they can see down below on the opium farm - Chinese soldiers with outdated weapons.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank tips his head to Nate at some other figures below -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: They ain't Chinese.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A handful of better-armed American sentries at the perimeter of the farm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CIA.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank, Nate and the others hang back as one of the Thais steps ahead to speak to the guerillas.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: C56 EXT. OPIUM FARM - LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The processing center for the entire region.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Thai translator is with Frank to negotiate with a vanquished Chinese general.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Other Americans and Thais guard them while the Chinese with their CIA advisors guard them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 24.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: D56 INT. BAMBOO DWELLING - LATER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Chinese general examines Frank's papers - passport, visa, bank receipts - and lots of cash - then studies Frank.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: How would you get it into the States?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: What do you care?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: Who do you work for in there?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: What do you care?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: Who are you really?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: It says right there.
{DIALOGUE}: Frank Lucas.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: I mean, who you represent?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man doesn't believe it, but lets it go.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: You think you're going to take a hundred kilos of heroin into the US and you don't work for anyone?
{DIALOGUE}: Someone is going to allow that?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank shrugs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The general regards one of his men.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In Chinese, subtitled:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: I don't believe a word of this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The general regards the cash and paperwork again for a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And, to Frank:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: After this first purchase, if you're not killed by Marseilles importers - or their people in the States - then what?
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 25.
{META_DATA}: D56 CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Then there'd be more.
{DIALOGUE}: On a regular basis.
{DIALOGUE}: Though I'd rather not have to drag my ass all the way up here every time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man regards Frank for a long moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Glances back to the cash and paperwork again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: Of course not.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: E56 EXT. JUNGLE ARMY LZ - VIETNAM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Torrential monsoon rains.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dripping camouflage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nate and Frank climb down from the Huey.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank no longer wears the bandolier.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now a press card dangles from his neck.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: F56 INT/EXT. TENT / JUNGLE ARMY LZ - LATER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stripes on the uniform of a black colonel with Nate under a canopy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Outside, in the distance, in the rain, Frank hangs out with some other black servicemen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLONEL
{DIALOGUE}: Where's it now?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NATE
{DIALOGUE}: Bangkok.
{DIALOGUE}: I can bring it here or anywhere in between.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLONEL
{DIALOGUE}: A hundred kilos.
{META_DATA}: (Nate nods)
{DIALOGUE}: I never seen that much dope in one place.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NATE
{DIALOGUE}: It's bigger than an Amana refrigerator- freezer.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: G56 INT/EXT. JUNGLE ARMY LZ - LATER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nate and Frank watch the colonel emerge from the tent and cross through the rain on duck-boards to another tent to speak with a white officer, a 2-star general.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NATE
{DIALOGUE}: Fifty grand.
{DIALOGUE}: In advance.
{DIALOGUE}: That'll cover them, the pilots and the guys on the other end.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Give them a hundred.
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 26.
{META_DATA}: G56 CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NATE
{DIALOGUE}: Fifty, to cover them all.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: A hundred.
{DIALOGUE}: And it's all I got left.
{DIALOGUE}: So if that dope doesn't arrive, for whatever reason -
{META_DATA}: (embraces Nate and whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: Cousin or no cousin - don't let me down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds out a business envelope fat with money.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nate hesitates, knowing Frank has just said he'll kill him if things don't go right, then takes it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NATE
{DIALOGUE}: I'll let you know when it's in the air.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 56 INT. RICHIE'S APARTMENT - NEWARK - DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The nurse/paramedic who stitched up his hand is in Richie's bed making so much noise he's worried someone will call the cops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The phone rings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And won't stop.
