{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Out front, a caravan of cars and pickup trucks - North Carolina plates - loaded with boxes and suitcases - has just arrived.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exhausted from the drive but excited to be here, the travelers climb out: Frank's five brothers, their wives and kids, and their mother.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy thinks it's the right place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The others aren't as sure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The house is too nice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a new Lincoln Towncar parked outside the garage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They'll probably be shot for trespassing.
