{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Our mandate is to make major arrests.
{DIALOGUE}: No street guys - we want the suppliers - the distributors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spearman, Jones and Abruzzo sit in the back, looking like delinquent students.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Of everyone in the open ground-floor that's been only slightly renovated - and there are about fifteen of them - they're the most disreputable-looking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Heroin, cocaine, amphetamines.
{DIALOGUE}: No grass under a thousand pounds.
{DIALOGUE}: Less than that, someone else can waste their time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jones nudges Abruzzo to pay attention.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Abruzzo elbows him back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie just waits like a teacher for their attention.
