{DIALOGUE}: I'll give you the other half tomorrow when you give -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MECHANIC
{DIALOGUE}: No, no, no, I don't do that.
{DIALOGUE}: Go fuck yourself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie rather reluctantly hands over the rest of the 20K.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 143 INT/EXT. SPEARMAN'S CAR - MOVING - NEAR GW BRIDGE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spearman watches the pickup truck driven by the mechanic change lanes up ahead - heading for the George Washington Bridge - and glances over concerned to Richie, who is changing the cashmere sweater for an old t-shirt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPEARMAN
{DIALOGUE}: He's going into New York.
{DIALOGUE}: Are we?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: What are they going to do, arrest us?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPEARMAN
{DIALOGUE}: They could.
{DIALOGUE}: New York cops.
{DIALOGUE}: They can do worse than that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: We're not losing that money.
{DIALOGUE}: Go.
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 58.
{META_DATA}: 143 CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Spearman follows the truck, the George Washington Bridge, linking Jersey to Manhattan, looms in the windshield ...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 144 EXT. EAST HARLEM STREET - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pickup pulls to the curb outside a Pleasant Avenue grocery store.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the guy enters the place, Spearman's car stops long enough for Richie to climb out, and continues on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie crosses the street, tries to see who the guy is talking to inside, but he's just buying a cup of coffee to go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spearman's car turns the corner to circle around the block.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As soon as it's gone, the man emerges from the restaurant with the coffee and walks straight at Richie who has to double back quickly not to be seen
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie sees a delivery truck double-parked, guys unloading crates.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hears a horn and knows it's must be Spearman stuck on the side street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mechanic starts his truck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Desperate not to lose him (and his money), Richie hurries over to a taxi stopped at a light, flashes his badge.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Get out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TAXI DRIVER
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Get the fuck out of the car!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The driver realizes the man outside his taxi is crazy and tries to get his window rolled up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reaching in, Richie gets his arm stuck, pulls at the lock, yanks the door open, drags the driver out, breaking the cabbie's arm, and jumps in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He swings the cab into opposing lanes to get around traffic, screeches around the corner, glimpses the truck far up ahead - guns the engine, flies through a red light, glances at his mirror at the cars that just missed him almost colliding -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The truck turns up ahead, and Richie barrels through another red light, turns the corner and keeps the truck, a couple car-lengths ahead - in sight.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 145 EXT. EAST HARLEM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie curbs the cab as the guy goes into a dingy pizza parlor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie climbs out, crosses the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coming past the place, he tries to look inside without breaking stride.
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 59.
{META_DATA}: 145 CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From around a corner, striding toward him, come four men looking like Gestapo thugs in leather coats, manicured hair - the Princes of the City.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie detours into an alley as they enter the restaurant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie peers in at the restaurant kitchen through a grimy basement window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Watches Trupo and his SIU detectives burst in, guns drawn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They rough everybody up, get some down on the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One detective gathers the money and stuffs it in a bag.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another gathers the dope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mechanic tries to protest and Trupo slaps him down with his pistol.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie keeps watching as the NY cops arrest no one - but take the dope and the money (Richie's money) - and stride out as abruptly as they appeared, like bandits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they come past Richie -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: That's my money.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SIU DET 1
{DIALOGUE}: The fuck are you.
{DIALOGUE}: What money?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie shows them his Bureau of Narcotics ID.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: The bills are sequenced and registered with the Essex County Prosecutors Office.
{DIALOGUE}: All begin with CF3500.
{DIALOGUE}: Take a look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of them checks some of the bills and sees he's right.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SIU DET. 2
{DIALOGUE}: Goddamn it, I thought we had a score.
{DIALOGUE}: I thought I had a fucking Chris-Craft sitting in my driveway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Honest mistake.
{DIALOGUE}: Just give it back to me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SIU DET. 1
{DIALOGUE}: This time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Three of the four cops laugh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's an affable gang of thieves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The one who doesn't laugh hangs back as the others start off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He examines Richie's New Jersey ID.
