{DIALOGUE}: There can be a camera on them they'll do it.
{DIALOGUE}: Some'll never do it.
{DIALOGUE}: The rest are capable of either, depending how their department leans ... Only theirs isn't leaning, it's fallen over.
{DIALOGUE}: The patrol cars don't even stop in Harlem, just roll down the window so the dealers can throw the money in.
