{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANA
{DIALOGUE}: I bought you something, too.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She crosses past the TV, takes a garment bag down from her side of the closet, lays it on the bed next to Frank's suit jacket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes hold of the zipper but doesn't immediately pull it, hoping perhaps to create some dramatic tension.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: What is it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She unzips the bag like she's unveiling great art.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But instead of seeing what's inside, we're allowed only Frank's reaction: his smile of anticipation slowly changing to chagrin.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 166 INT/EXT. MADISON SQUARE GARDEN - BACK ENTRANCE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie observes celebrities and gangsters arriving in limousines - Sammy Davis Jr. and his wife, Joe Louis and his, Tosca and some of his guys - then enters the arena as another limo pulls up.
