{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 69.
{META_DATA}: 167 CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The owner of the gleaming patent leather shoes is shown to his second row ringside seat just behind the sports writers, and we move up the full-length chinchilla coat to Frank's uneasy expression -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie's camera roams the faces of the prime ticket holders ringside: organized crime figures, celebrities, politicians, women with plunging necklines and platinum hair -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOE LOUIS
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie can't believe it's Joe Louis brushing past him -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Louis -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Joe looks back as Richie approaches him -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, but I just have to tell you, sir, you were a hero to me growing up.
{DIALOGUE}: I still push elevator buttons eight times for the rounds you beat Billy Conn in.
{DIALOGUE}: For luck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Louis acknowledges Richie only slightly more than not at all.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Turns away to join his friends.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie watches after him, stung by Louis's disregard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He snaps a picture of an Italian wise guy he doesn't recognize ... sifts the camera's view past Frank in the chinchilla coat ... then returns to him, watches as Tosca and his guys sit down behind Frank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie can't hear - but can see - their good-natured exchange -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOSCA
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, Frank, you keep that hat on, I'm gonna miss the fight -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The odd thing to Richie is, Chinchilla's seat is better than all the Italians'.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Detective Trupo notices this, too.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie focuses on the Chincilla's date, a stunning girl, a beauty queen, then shifts back to her boyfriend who's now shaking the proffered hands of other Italians, then Don King.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Joe Louis himself - who barely acknowledged Richie's existence - comes over and playfully exchanges "punches" with the man in the chinchilla coat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A sudden roar from the crowd as the lights go out except for the spot on the ring.
