{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Nights, he usually stays home.
{DIALOGUE}: When he does go out, it's to a club or dinner - with his new wife - friends, celebrities, sports figures - never O.C. guys.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 187 EXT. SMALL'S PARADISE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie sits in his car across from Small's where bouncers keep out people like him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank, Ana, Wilt Chamberlain and his wife emerge from the restaurant together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 188 OMIT 188 OMIT
{META_DATA}: 189 INT. NARCOTICS SQUAD HQ - NEWARK - CONTINUED
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Sundays he takes his mother to church.
{DIALOGUE}: Then drives out to change the flowers on Bumpy's grave.
{DIALOGUE}: Every Sunday, no matter what.
{META_DATA}: 190 INT. BAPTIST CHURCH - CONTINUED - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank's mother tearfully watches her son slip a ring onto Ana's finger next to the fat engagement diamond - before Ana, in turn, puts a gold band on Frank's.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The minister pronounces them husband and wife, the veil is lifted, and they kiss to great applause -
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 191 EXT. BAPTIST CHURCH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As a photographer takes the official photograph of the wedding party on the steps of the church -
{META_DATA}: 192 INT. NARCOTICS SQUAD HQ - NEWARK - CONTINUED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lou Toback looks from a surveillance photo of the wedding party in his hands, to Richie's Table of Organization: The Lucas brothers and cousins - in the streets of New York and New Jersey, arranged in some imagined hierarchy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOBACK
{DIALOGUE}: Not your typical day in the life of a dope man, Richie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Neither was Bumpy Johnson's and he owned Harlem.
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 74.
{META_DATA}: 192 CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOBACK
{DIALOGUE}: You think Frank Lucas took over for Bumpy Johnson?
