{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHARLIE
{DIALOGUE}: She's the most beautiful bride I ever saw, Frank.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: I wish Bumpy could've met her.
{DIALOGUE}: I wish she could've met him.
{META_DATA}: 194 INT. NARCOTICS SQUAD HQ - NEWARK - CONTINUED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looking at the Lucas Table of Organization -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOBACK
{DIALOGUE}: What do you got on him you can use in court?
{DIALOGUE}: Because this isn't it.
{DIALOGUE}: You try this without informants and powder, no one's going to jail.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Won't get any informants.
{DIALOGUE}: Not inside.
{DIALOGUE}: It's like a Sicilian family.
{DIALOGUE}: Like he's structured his own family the same way to protect himself.
{META_DATA}: 195 EXT. BAPTIST CHURCH - CONTINUED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exactly like one, like a scene from The Godfather as Frank dances with Ana before the reception guests.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 75.
{META_DATA}: 196 INT. NARCOTICS SQUAD HQ - NEWARK - CONTINUED
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Being with Bumpy long as he was, he would have been around Italians a lot.
{DIALOGUE}: Enough to learn that much.
{META_DATA}: 197 EXT. BAPTIST CHURCH - CONTINUED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rice rains down on the bride and groom as they climb into the back of the Towncar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Doc comes around to the driver's side, gets in and slowly pushes through the crush of guests waving and throwing kisses.
{META_DATA}: 198 INT. NARCOTICS SQUAD HQ - NEWARK - CONTINUED
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: But it's not even Frank Lucas I want.
{DIALOGUE}: I want to know who he's working for: Which Italians are bringing the heroin in.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 199 INT/EXT. TOWNCAR / NEW YORK - TWILIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flanked front and rear by Frank's security, the marriage car moves along a rain-slick street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The newlyweds cuddle in back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another car pulls up alongside - Trupo's Shelby - and Doc's right hand instinctively comes off the steering wheel to settle on his holstered gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Trupo smiles and shakes his head, no.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 200 EXT. CENTRAL PARK - LATER - TWILIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Lincoln and security cars and Trupo's Shelby parked.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{META_DATA}: (to Ana)
{DIALOGUE}: Stay in the car
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Frank and Doc climb out, Frank motions to his other security men to remain calm, he'll handle this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRUPO
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, Frank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: If Frank is surprised Trupo knows his name, he doesn't show it, or anything else except an air of professional courtesy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Detective.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Trupo looks in at Ana in the back seat, smiles at her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns her head away and closes the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Trupo leads Frank away for a private conversation -
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 76.
{META_DATA}: 200 CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRUPO
{DIALOGUE}: You sure you done the right thing?
{DIALOGUE}: She's a beautiful girl - there's no question - but she's got an attitude on (her) -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Listen to me.
{DIALOGUE}: Before you say another word - about her - or me - remember that you're saying it on the most important fuckin day of my life.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRUPO
{DIALOGUE}: Man walks around in a fifty thousand dollar chinchilla coat and he never even bought me a cup of coffee?
{DIALOGUE}: Something wrong there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know what you're talking about.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRUPO
{DIALOGUE}: You pay your bills, Frank?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: You want to keep talking, talk to my lawyer, here's his card.
