{DIALOGUE}: From who, your uncle?
{META_DATA}: (Tony doesn't say)
{DIALOGUE}: Why would you do this?
{DIALOGUE}: Why would you risk our friendship?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: Because I care what happens to you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: You shouldn't have done it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: I had to.
{DIALOGUE}: I had no choice.
{DIALOGUE}: Neither do you.
{DIALOGUE}: Leave Frank Lucas alone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: He's not important enough for you to do this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, he is.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie stares at Tony, then puts the pictures in his hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Tell Marie I'm sorry I had to leave.
{DIALOGUE}: You can tell her why.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 89.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 226 INT. NARCOTICS SQUAD HQ - LATER - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Alone in the empty building, he stares at the T.O.: The higher echelon Italians like Tosca; lower echelon Harlem guys like Charlie Williams and Frank Lucas.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets up then, untacks Frank's photograph from its lowly position and moves it to a place no black has ever occupied - to the top of the pyramid - above the mafia.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 227 - 230 OMIT 227 - 230 OMIT
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A231 INT. NARCOTICS SQUAD HQ - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toback regards Frank's picture at top of the Lucas T.O.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: INS, FBI, IRS - I can't get anything out of them.
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing on his travel, his bank accounts, property holdings - nothing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOBACK
{DIALOGUE}: That's because they all think you're on the take and you think they are.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: They don't want this to stop.
{DIALOGUE}: It employs too many people.
{DIALOGUE}: Cops, lawyers, judges, probation officers, prison guards.
{DIALOGUE}: The day dope stops coming into this country, a hundred thousand people lose their jobs.
{DIALOGUE}: Toback isn't as sure the corruption of the official world is that complete.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPEARMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Richie.
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spearman gestures to a couple of men in suits who want to talk to him.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: B231 INT. NARCOTICS SQUAD HQ - LATER - DAY
