{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 101.
{META_DATA}: 266 CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Just like that?
{DIALOGUE}: We're going to leave the fuckin country to the communists?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NATE
{DIALOGUE}: We been here since 1961, Frank.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: I haven't!
{META_DATA}: HARD CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 267 EXT. JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank and Nate and their "army" of black servicemen and Thai thugs wind through the jungle with pack mules.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 268 INT. BAMBOO DWELLING - OPIUM FARM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The same farm and hut as before.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank and the Chinese General sip tea.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The four million dollars in cash Frank brought sits on the table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: Opium plants are hearty enough to outlive any war.
{DIALOGUE}: They'll still be here long after the troops are gone.
{DIALOGUE}: But what are you going to do for transportation when the last US plane goes home?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: I'll figure something out.
{DIALOGUE}: You'll see me again.
{DIALOGUE}: The General seems fond of Frank, and not only because of all the money on the table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: It's not in my best interest to say this, Frank ... but quitting while you're ahead is not the same as quitting.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: That's what my wife thinks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GENERAL
{DIALOGUE}: But you don't think she's right.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank doesn't say.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 102.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 269 EXT. OPIUM FARM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mules are loaded up with burlap bags containing 3,000 kilos of heroin.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A270 EXT. OPIUM FARM / JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mule train approaches the jungle that surrounds the opium farm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nate's Thai thugs, left behind in sniper positions in the trees, stand ready to open fire if they have to as Frank, Nate, the soldiers and mules pass below.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: B270 EXT. JUNGLE - LATER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They seem to have made it, winding back down through the jungle with the mules.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly a barrage of gunfire erupts from the trees - a couple of Nate's men are hit as the rest dive for cover, shouting "Vietcong," and returning the fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank drops down from his mule, gets a pistol out and shoots into the trees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bullet-severed palm fronds rain down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Give them half!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nate, pinned down by the mules, can't hear him over the noise.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Cut half of them loose!
{DIALOGUE}: The mules!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nate cuts the mule-train tether in the middle, slaps at the animals.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the freed mules disappear into a wall of trees the shooting subsides, then stops altogether.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Smoke from all the gunfire rises like mist around the half dozen Thais and Americans lying dead on the ground.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 270 EXT. STREET - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teddy makes out with a girl in the back seat of his car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pay phone just outside on the corner rings, and he gets out, steps past Jimmy, answers it -
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 271 INT. SOUL BROTHERS BAR - BANGKOK - INTERCUT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A Thai singer attempts Otis Redding on the little stage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frank, at a table here, with a drink and a phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Newark.
{DIALOGUE}: Short Term Parking Lot 3.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TEDDY V/O
{DIALOGUE}: When you need it?
{DIALOGUE}: Today?
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 103.
{META_DATA}: 271 CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANK
{DIALOGUE}: Tomorrow will be fine.
{META_DATA}: 272 EXT. STREET - CONTINUED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jimmy loiters close enough to the open pay phone, to hear Teddy's side of the conversation.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TEDDY
{DIALOGUE}: Short Term Lot 3.
{DIALOGUE}: This the Mustang were talking about ... Camero?
{DIALOGUE}: ... What's the plate number?
{META_DATA}: (writes on a napkin)
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I got it ... I got it, Frank ...
{META_DATA}: (sighs; reads from the napkin:)
{DIALOGUE}: KA 760.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 273 INT. NARCOTICS SQUAD HQ - NEWARK - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jimmy's come over to share his news with the detectives.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But Richie isn't pleased with it - or with Jimmy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ABRUZZO
