{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 282 INT. AIRPORT HANGAR - LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The plane has been brought into a hangar where it's being taken apart like a car stripped by thieves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Inside the cabin, seats are removed and inspected, carpeting pulled up, panels unscrewed, lavatories dismantled.
{META_DATA}: 283 INT. MAMA LUCAS'S TEANECK, N.J. HOUSE - CONTINUED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Downstairs - Ana and Frank's mother, guarded, can hear Trupo and his detectives, upstairs, ransacking a bedroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Upstairs - the SIU detectives pull open drawers, throw clothes from the closets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Trupo picks up an invitation to a United Nations ball, tosses it down again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finds a safety- deposit box key in a sock drawer, puts it in his pocket.
{META_DATA}: 284 INT. AIRPORT HANGAR - CONTINUED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The engines and landing gear are disassembled, the tires opened up and searched.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A nozzle plunges into a toilet and pumps out the contents into barrels detectives fish through with gloved hands -
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 285 INT. MAMA LUCAS'S TEANECK, N.J. HOUSE - LATER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ana is taken upstairs, brought before the SIU detectives who wait for the NYPD cops to leave the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The place has been torn apart.
