{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 108.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 298 INT. AIRPORT HANGER OFFICE - MINUTES LATER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie and Toback sit before the Federal Attorneys and customs agents.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The US Attorney hangs up a phone ... then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: US ATTORNEY
{DIALOGUE}: That was a military transport plane.
{DIALOGUE}: If there was heroin on board then someone in the military would have to be involved.
{DIALOGUE}: Which means that even as it fights a war that's claimed 50,000 Americans lives, the military is smuggling narcotics.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie's in serious trouble and knows it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As does Toback.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: US ATTORNEY
{DIALOGUE}: That's how these events are being interpreted by General Easton in that call to me.
{DIALOGUE}: That someone employed by the this office believes the United States Army is in the drug trafficking business - and is trying to prove it by desecrating the remains of young men who've given their lives in the defence of democracy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: There are drugs on that plane -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: US ATTORNEY
{DIALOGUE}: Shut the fuck up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie does, but can't conceal the contempt he feels for these men who've never spent a minute on the street but act as if know more than him, and who are, in the unfortunate organization of his world, his superiors.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: US ATTORNEY
{DIALOGUE}: Is it any wonder then, because of your actions, the entire federal narcotics program is now in jeopardy of being dismantled as completely and enthusiastic- ally as that fucking transport plane?
{DIALOGUE}: That's what you've accomplished Mr. Roberts.
{DIALOGUE}: Single-handedly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: I had good information the target of my investigation was bringing dope in on that plane.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: US ATTORNEY
{DIALOGUE}: And that target is?
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 109.
{META_DATA}: 298 CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: Frank Lucas.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one in the room, except Richie and Toback, has ever heard the name.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The federal men regard one another blankly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: US ATTORNEY
{DIALOGUE}: Who?
{DIALOGUE}: Who's Frank Lucas?
{META_DATA}: (no one seems to know)
{DIALOGUE}: Who's he work for?
{DIALOGUE}: Which family?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: He's not Italian.
{DIALOGUE}: He's black.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now there's a longer, even deeper silence, before -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: US ATTORNEY
{DIALOGUE}: Is that supposed to be some kind of joke?
{DIALOGUE}: You're this close to the end of your career in law enforcement, you're making jokes?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: I believe Frank Lucas is above the mafia in the dope business.
{DIALOGUE}: I believe he buys direct from the source in Southeast Asia, cuts out all the middlemen, and uses US military planes and personnel to bring pure No. 4 heroin into United States.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Richie is looking at faces that are still trying to make sense out of his ridiculous theory.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toback tries to come to his defense -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOBACK
{DIALOGUE}: Richie has a lot of experience -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: US ATTORNEY
{DIALOGUE}: Does he.
{DIALOGUE}: And how many arrests has he made in his so-called investigation?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: I was promised when I took this job, it was about real arrests.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: US ATTORNEY
{DIALOGUE}: Does that mean `none?'
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RICHIE
{DIALOGUE}: I have cases against most of Frank's organization.
{DIALOGUE}: Not him -
{META_DATA}: (CONT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 110.
